law.text:
The jury plan of a circuit court may provide for an agreement between the circuit court and the Administrative Office of the Courts or a person, for the Administrative Office or person to:
Provide the circuit court with names selected in the number that the jury plan sets;
Have juror questionnaire forms sent as the jury plan requires;
Have summonses sent as the jury plan requires; or
Provide any other service as to jury selection and service.
